 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               7425 1451
                                                                  7425 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                7425 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               7425 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             7425 1451
                                                                  7425 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              7425 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b35 by                    7425 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               7425 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               7425 1451
 and features:                                                    7425 1451
                                                                  7425 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 7425 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         7425 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    7425 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              7425 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                7425 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      7425 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   7425 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                7425 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               7425 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      7425 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 7425 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                7425 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   7425 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                7425 1451
   discrete transitions                                           7425 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              7425 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                7425 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               7425 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              7425 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 7425 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              7425 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           7425 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    7425 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 7425 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                7425 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      7425 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        7425 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               7425 1451
